articles.title: Almaty airport says 7 killed in Kazakhstan plane crash
articles.description: Almaty International Airport said nine people died on Friday in the crash of a Bek Air plane in Kazakhstan.
articles.content:
A Bek Air plane crashed into a two-story building in Kazakhstan shortly after takeoff Friday, killing at least nine and prompting a massive rescue effort. 
There were 100 passengers and crew aboard.
